Founded as a spin-off from CNRS lab Institut Langevin, OWLO is building next generation microscopy for healthcare. 
 
 Our unique technology is the first to provide real-time 3D imaging in a non invasive way. Powered by AI image analysis, this innovation will change research and medical practice by making visible and quantifying what was previously unseen.
 
 Our first use case is in Assisted Reproductive Technologies (ART) where 75% of embryos transfers fail today, resulting in long and expensive procedures that are very stressful and demanding for women. We provide an entirely new way of looking at embryos with new indicators to predict their viability before implantation to improve the efficiency of the procedure and reduce its cost.

column5: Our geochemistry laboratory is a leading specialist in the field of hydrothermal alteration and hydrogen-optimized production from rocks. Together, let's become players in the production of natural H2, for a new low-carbon energy mix.
column7: My research focuses on processes that help to optimize hydrogen production in ultrabasic reservoirs. This is based on experimental approaches to rock alteration and oxidation processes, such as serpentinization. My main interests are in quantifying hydrogen production and consumption, and CO‚ÇÇ storage by mineralization. My experiments allow me to analyze the entire system and compare the initial and final mineral assemblies. Thus, the production of H‚ÇÇ as a function of the different tested parameters can be compared. I am currently working on developing an experimental geochemistry start-up called RockyH2. This is based on the work of my former thesis supervisors, Pr. Muriel Andreani and Dr. Eric C Gaucher (who are also the founders), as well as my own work. RockyH2 aims to become a major player in the sector of optimized/stimulated production of natural hydrogen from rocks or materials, alongside synchronous CO‚ÇÇ storage under mineral or reduced forms. Positioned at the interface between academia and industry, this initiative will develop innovative engineering, chemical and physical solutions to optimize and stimulate hydrogen production.

Credit for the background image: @mikehankin." -------------- Hello, I'm Laure. I'm a full time climate activist. It's ok, don't get scared ! About us
 
 As an independent and non-profit research organization, we believe that political crises cannot be understood without a deep grasp for the dynamics on the ground.
 
 Our primary mandates are to translate data gathered on the ground into original analyses, and to leverage our research for the purpose of informing policy debates and engaging wider audiences
 
 This is why we are doctrinally committed to field-based research. Cognizant that knowledge ought to benefit society, we also pledge to impact civil society organizations, policymakers, and the general public.
 
 Our mission:
 
 1. Investigate: Build and fund research programs that enable long-term projects to be undertaken, led by international teams.
 2. Train: Support young researchers and promote a common methodology for fieldwork.
 3. Disseminate: Design and create innovative, accessible formats to promote the inclusion of field research in public debate, in France and internationally.
